Citation.sTitle: Solubility of Thiotriazinone in Binary Solvent Mixtures of Water + Methanol and Water + Ethanol from (283 to 330) K
Citation.sAbstract: The solubility of thiotriazinone in water, methanol, ethanol, water + methanol, and water + ethanol has been measured under temperatures ranging from (283 to 330) K with a laser technique. The results of these measurements were correlated with semiempirical equations. The calculated results have showed fine representativity of experimental data. The stepwise regression method was used to simplify the modified Jouyban Acree equation.
